</section>
<div class="distance-bar">💼 WEEKLY FROM $588 · MONTHLY RATES AVAILABLE · KITCHENETTES · FREE BREAKFAST</div>
<div class="content-wrap">
<div class="intro-pull"><strong>Extended stays in Vernal don't have to mean apartment hunting or bare-bones motels.</strong> Best Western Vernal Inn offers weekly rates starting at $588 for a Standard Queen room (that's $84/night) and $660 for a Double Queen — with full kitchenettes, free hot breakfast every morning, free laundry, free parking, and free WiFi all included. For oilfield rotations, construction projects, temporary relocations, and seasonal work in the Uintah Basin, our extended-stay option eliminates the hassle of finding short-term housing.</div>
<div class="content-section">
 <h2>What Makes Our Extended Stay Different</h2>
<p>Most Vernal hotels offer a nightly rate and nothing else. Best Western Vernal Inn is set up for guests who stay weeks and months, not just nights. Kitchenette rooms have a full-size refrigerator, microwave, stovetop, and basic cookware — so you can cook real meals instead of spending $30–$50/day eating out. Free breakfast every morning means one meal is already handled. On-site laundry means you don't need to haul clothes across town. And our front desk staff knows extended-stay guests by name.</p>
<ul class="feat-list">
 <li>Weekly rates: Standard Queen $588 · Double Queen $660</li>
 <li>Monthly rates available — call (435) 789-6625 for pricing</li>
 <li>Full kitchenettes — refrigerator, microwave, stovetop, cookware</li>
 <li>Free hot breakfast every morning — eggs, waffles, coffee, juice</li>
 <li>Free on-site laundry facilities</li>
 <li>Free WiFi — strong enough for video calls and remote work</li>
 <li>Free parking — trucks, trailers, and work vehicles welcome</li>
 <li>Pet friendly — dogs welcome with a small fee</li>
 <li>24-hour front desk — flexible schedules for shift workers</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="content-section">
 <h2>Who Stays Extended at Best Western Vernal Inn</h2>
<p>Our extended-stay guests include oilfield workers on 2-week and 4-week rotations flying into Vernal Regional Airport (just 0.6 miles away), pipeline and construction crews working seasonal projects in the Uintah Basin, government and BLM field staff on temporary assignments, families in between homes during relocation, and traveling nurses and healthcare workers stationed at Ashley Regional Medical Center. The common thread is people who need more than a hotel room — they need a temporary home.</p>
<ul class="feat-list">
 <li>Oilfield workers on rotating crew schedules</li>
 <li>Pipeline, construction, and utility contractors</li>
 <li>Government and BLM field personnel</li>
 <li>Traveling nurses and healthcare professionals</li>
 <li>Families relocating to the Uintah Basin</li>
 <li>Seasonal workers — hunting guides, outdoor recreation staff</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="pro-tip"><p><strong>Extended Stay Tip:</strong> For stays of 14+ nights, call (435) 789-6625 and ask about monthly pricing. Our best rates are always available by phone, not online — because we work with you directly to find the right room and the right price for your timeline.</p></div>
<div class="content-section">
 <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
